:144},[45,1466,438],{"class":137},[45,1468,1469],{"class":47,"line":229},[45,1470,642],{"class":137},[45,1472,1473],{"class":47,"line":237},[45,1474,212],{"class":137},[45,1476,1477],{"class":47,"line":243},[45,1478,160],{"emptyLinePlaceholder":159},[45,1480,1481,1483,1485],{"class":47,"line":628},[45,1482,432],{"class":137},[45,1484,435],{"class":144},[45,1486,438],{"class":137},[12,1488,1489],{},"The other scraper for article details follows the same pattern — leaving that as practice for you.",[20,1491,1493],{"id":1492},"a-bit-of-confusion","A bit of confusion",[12,1495,1496],{},"There might be some confusion now: what's the difference between Node.js Cron and Linux Cron?",[12,1498,1499],{},[15,1500],{"alt":1501,"src":1502},"Confusion","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002Fblog\u002Fnodejs\u002Fithelp-nodejs-2023\u002F1694788997653.png",[12,1504,1505,1506,1508],{},"The ",[42,1507,92],{}," package we install via npm runs in the Node.js environment, while Linux is an operating system. They're not the same thing — just the concepts and time format are similar, which causes confusion sometimes.",[12,1510,1511,1512,1515],{},"So you usually see people saying ",[42,1513,1514],{},"node-cron",", but it's because the npm install command is:",[35,1517,1518],{"className":37,"code":96,"language":39,"meta":40,"style":40},[42,1519,1520],{"__ignoreMap":40},[45,1521,1522,1524,1526],{"class":47,"line":48},[45,1523,71],{"class":51},[45,1525,105],{"class":55},[45,1527,108],{"class":55},[12,1529,1530],{},"Hence the confusion. But these are different things — just similar in concept.",[12,1532,1533],{},"What's the obvious difference? As mentioned, the concepts and time formats are very similar. But Linux Cron is more often used to run Shell Scripts, so compared to Node.js Cron, it's harder to extend with more complex logic.",[440,1535,1536],{},[12,1537,1538,1540,1541,939,1544,939,1546,1548],{},[445,1539,447],{},"\nShell Script is a plain text file containing commands like ",[42,1542,1543],{},"ls",[42,1545,63],{},[42,1547,52],{},", etc. — commands that run in the terminal. Think of Shell Script as a file you can run in the terminal.",[12,1550,1551,1552,1554],{},"In short: if you want to run your own JavaScript code in Node.js, use ",[42,1553,1514],{},". If you want to run Shell Scripts on Linux, use Linux Cron.",[12,1556,1557],{},"That's it for this post, see you in the next one.",[1559,1560,1561],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .s_sBn, html code.shiki .s_sBn{--shiki-default:#FFB757}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html pre.shiki code .sWyjQ, html code.shiki .sWyjQ{--shiki-default:#FF9492}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sj_SG, html code.shiki .sj_SG{--shiki-default:#DBB7FF}html pre.shiki code .sQrFR, html code.shiki .sQrFR{--shiki-default:#BDC4CC}",{"title":40,"searchDepth":59,"depth":59,"links":1563},[1564,1565,1566,1567,1568],{"id":22,"depth":59,"text":23},{"id":29,"depth":59,"text":30},{"id":111,"depth":59,"text":112},{"id":458,"depth":59,"text":459},{"id":1492,"depth":59,"text":1493},"Nodejs","2023-10-03 00:00:01","In the previous post we got a basic concept of Crontab. Now of course we need to apply it to a real example, otherwise knowing it isn't useful. So this post implements a Crontab + Node.js example.","md","en",{},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002Fday-19-crontab-plus-nodejs","4",{"title":6,"descript